==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Thiosulphate
<hw>Thi`o*sul"phate</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Chem.)</fld>
<def>A salt of thiosulphuric acid; -- formerly called
<altname>hyposulphite</altname>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><note>⟦hand⟧ The sodium salt called in photography by the name
<xex>sodium hyposulphite</xex>, being used as a solvent for the excess
of unchanged silver chloride, bromide, and iodide on the sensitive
plate.</note>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Thiosulphuric</ent>⟦br⟧
